Subject: [PATCH] aic8800: fix pointer comparison in wext helper

The existing condition checking for the BSSID pointer compares the
address of the first element in the array, which is always non-null and
causes newer compilers to fail the build with -Werror=address. Only test
for the presence of the scan result entry itself before copying the
address.

Upstream-Status: Pending

--- a/aic8800_fdrv/aicwf_wext_linux.c
+++ b/aic8800_fdrv/aicwf_wext_linux.c
@@ -400,8 +400,8 @@
 	iwe->cmd = SIOCGIWAP;
 	iwe->u.ap_addr.sa_family = ARPHRD_ETHER;
 
-	if(scan_re->bss && &scan_re->bss->bssid[0]){
-	memcpy(iwe->u.ap_addr.sa_data, scan_re->bss->bssid, ETH_ALEN);
+	if (scan_re->bss) {
+		memcpy(iwe->u.ap_addr.sa_data, scan_re->bss->bssid, ETH_ALEN);
 	}
 
 	start = iwe_stream_add_event(info, start, stop, iwe, IW_EV_ADDR_LEN);
